      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Yet it can be argued that the multipliers that the typical New-Keynesian model produces understate the impact of fiscal policy in the context of zero-bound interest rates and/or recession. The basic Dynamic Stochastic General Equilibrium (DSGE) model solves on a local linearised path of a system of non-linear equations thus the effects of fiscal expansion on consumption or output are the same whether the economy is in a roaring boom or a deep recession. [CITATION_1] argues that the multiplier should be state-dependent and calls for research into non-linear systems."
